  "texts": [
    "In Martins et al. (2023), machine learning model artifacts created by students were used as evidence to demonstrate their learning outcomes.",
    "The performance-based assessment was used to evaluate students' ability to correctly label the recycling trash images in the classification process.",
    "The results of this study are consistent with Kandlhofer et al. (2016), who found that a variety of learning tools have been designed to support various learning objectives for students from kindergarten to university.",
    "The previous literature also indicates that many learning tools, such as intelligent agents and software, are effective in facilitating adolescents' and university students' acquisition of computational thinking skills (Çakiroğlu et al., 2018; Van Brummelen et al., 2021), whereas the availability of such tools for kindergarten and primary students is often overlooked.",
    "Few researchers have investigated whether AI learning tools can bridge the learning gap of younger students (Zhou et al., 2020)."
  ],
